item.title: How do i fix this?
item.dc:creator: @usman555 usman555
item.description:
@usman555 wrote:

[quote=“bily123, post:5, topic:350746”][quote author=iBuffo link=topic=447101.msg3282555#msg3282555 date=1279975325]
Your no-ip is probably set the same as the other server. Create a new no-ip and just edit your .java files, and paste in the new no-ip. but make the new no-ip use a different port, and portfoward for that port.
Your welcome
[/quote]
thanks but now im not too sure how to log onto my previousely made server. I changed the ip like the guide said to but how do i log into it with that ip? and how do i add objects such as alters?[/quote]
Don’t change the subject. But i’ll quickly answer
follow this void public void NewObjects() {
You will see some lines underneath that void that start with “makeGlobalObject” beside it, there are some numbers
integer one is the X position
integer two is the Y position
integer three is the Object ID
integer four is the orientation
integer five is the tileObjectType
